This paper proposes a new approach for generative adversarial networks (GANs) that reduces the dependence on labeled data. It incorporates the idea of updating centers in K-Means into GANs and redesigns the framework of GANs by applying K-Means on the features extracted from the discriminator. The paper also proposes new objective functions from the perspective of deep metric learning (DML). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, since the paper proposes a new approach for GANs, it could also be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
